    "title": "Same block hash",
    "body": "Today I was wondering once we get same hash for 2 different blocks, will the blockchain fork ? I know it has a small chance right now, but with the diff increase the chance is getting bigger, because the range of the accepted hashes are getting smaller. I am not sure if the same hash would break the integrity of blockchain, or would cause fork, but please look into it.\n",
