      "author_association": "MEMBER",
      "body": "The first thing AcceptBlock() does is check for duplicate block hashes and reject the block in that case. The blockchain will not fork, it will just not be accepted.\n\nHowever, as @christophebiocca says _If_ you're able to create double-SHA2 collisions, then you could create all kinds of havoc with the network. The algorithm will have to be switched way before then.\n",
